This SERVICE is provided by Paul Perepel at no cost and is intended for use “as is.”
By downloading, installing, or using our apps (“Service”), you agree to the collection and use of your information as described in this Privacy Policy. If you do not agree with our policies, please do not use our Service.
1. Information Collection and Use
Personal Data
For an enhanced user experience, we may request certain personally identifiable information (such as device identifiers or crash data) that is stored locally on your device.
We do not actively collect personal data for account creation or profiling purposes.
In cases where third-party services are integrated, those services may collect personal data as described in their respective privacy policies.
Non-Personal Data
We automatically collect non-personal information such as device type, operating system version, app configuration, and usage statistics (“Log Data”). This data helps us analyze usage trends and improve our Service.
2. Use of Third-Party Services
Our apps utilize third-party services that may collect information used to identify you. For example:
Google Play Services:
Used for authentication, analytics, and app functionality enhancements. Please review the respective privacy policies of these third-party providers for more details.
3. Log Data
In the event of an error or unexpected behavior, our apps may automatically log certain data (“Log Data”). This may include:
Your device’s Internet Protocol (IP) address
Device name and model
Operating system version
Time and date of app usage
Error reports and app configuration details
This data is used solely for diagnosing issues and improving the Service.
4. Cookies and Similar Technologies
While our apps do not use cookies in the traditional web sense, they may incorporate third-party code and libraries that use similar tracking technologies. These technologies may:
Assign anonymous identifiers to your device
Enhance and personalize your experience
Collect usage and performance data
You may choose to disable these features; however, this may limit the functionality of some aspects of our Service.
5. Service Providers
We may employ third-party companies and individuals to:
Facilitate our Service
Provide the Service on our behalf
Perform Service-related functions (such as analytics, advertising, and customer support)
Assist us in understanding how our Service is used
These third parties have access to your information only to perform these tasks on our behalf and are obligated not to disclose or use it for any other purpose.
6. Security
We value your trust and strive to use commercially acceptable means to protect your information. However, please note that no method of electronic storage or internet transmission is completely secure. We cannot guarantee absolute security.
7. User Rights and Data Retention
We are committed to transparency regarding your data:
Access & Correction:
You have the right to access and request corrections to your personal information.
Data Deletion:
If you wish to have your data removed, please contact us (see Contact Us below). Requests will be processed in accordance with applicable law.
Data Retention:
Log Data and other non-personal information may be retained for a reasonable period to help us maintain and improve our Service.
8. Links to Other Sites
Our apps may contain links to third-party websites or services that are not operated by us. We are not responsible for the content, privacy policies, or practices of these external sites. We encourage you to review the privacy policies of any third-party sites you visit.
9. Children’s Privacy
Our Service is not directed to individuals under 13 years of age. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13. If we become aware that personal data from a child under 13 has been inadvertently collected, we will promptly delete such information. If you are a parent or guardian and believe your child’s information has been collected, please contact us immediately.
10. Compliance with Google Play Policies
In addition to this Privacy Policy, our apps comply with all current Google Play Developer Program Policies. We have implemented the necessary measures to ensure transparency in data collection, user consent, and privacy practices as required by Google. This includes providing clear disclosures on data usage and user rights.
11. Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update our Privacy Policy periodically. Any changes will be posted on this page, and the “Effective Date” will be updated accordingly. We encourage you to review this Privacy Policy regularly for any updates.
